welcome_message_body: "Welcome to Westphalia, a charming city known for its rich history and friendly locals. Get ready to explore and experience all that our beautiful city has to offer. Enjoy your stay!"

terminals.name: Main Terminal
terminals.description: The main terminal at Potomac Airfield Airport serves all commercial flights.

terminals.name: Private Terminal
terminals.description: The private terminal at Potomac Airfield Airport caters to private and charter flights.

wifi.note: Free wifi is available throughout the airport.

terminals.name: Main Terminal
terminals.description: This terminal serves domestic flights and is the largest terminal at Reagan National Airport.

terminals.name: Terminal A
terminals.description: This terminal serves regional flights and is the smallest terminal at Reagan National Airport.

terminals.name: Terminal B
terminals.description: This terminal serves domestic flights and is the second largest terminal at Reagan National Airport.

terminals.name: Terminal C
terminals.description: This terminal serves domestic and international flights and is the newest terminal at Reagan National Airport.

wifi.note: WiFi is available throughout the airport and is free for all passengers.

terminals.name: Main Terminal
terminals.description: The main terminal at Tipton AAF Airport serves both commercial and military flights.

terminals.name: Military Terminal
terminals.description: The military terminal at Tipton AAF Airport is used exclusively for military flights and operations.

wifi.note: WiFi is available throughout the airport terminal.

terminals.name: Main Terminal
terminals.description: The main terminal at Lee Airport serves domestic flights and offers a variety of amenities for travelers.

terminals.name: General Aviation Terminal
terminals.description: The general aviation terminal at Lee Airport caters to private and charter flights, providing personalized services for passengers.

wifi.note: Free WiFi is available throughout the airport for all passengers.

terminals.name: Main Terminal
terminals.description: The main terminal at Baltimore/Washington International Thurgood Marshall Airport serves both domestic and international flights.

terminals.name: Concourse A
terminals.description: Concourse A at Baltimore/Washington International Thurgood Marshall Airport serves primarily Southwest Airlines flights.

terminals.name: Concourse B
terminals.description: Concourse B at Baltimore/Washington International Thurgood Marshall Airport serves primarily American Airlines flights.

terminals.name: Concourse C
terminals.description: Concourse C at Baltimore/Washington International Thurgood Marshall Airport serves primarily Spirit Airlines and United Airlines flights.

wifi.note: Passengers can access free WiFi throughout the airport by selecting the 'BWI Airport Free WiFi' network and agreeing to the terms and conditions.

terminals.name: Main Terminal
terminals.description: The main terminal at Montgomery County Airport serves all commercial and private flights.

terminals.name: Private Terminal
terminals.description: The private terminal at Montgomery County Airport caters to private and charter flights.

wifi.note: Free WiFi is available throughout the airport.
